The paper proposes a machine learning framework for optimal multi-target control in automatic driving based on knowledge acquisition. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the control of complex driving environments, which falls under the sub-category of Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of GPU for high-performance computing, which is relevant to Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of multiple objective functions, which is relevant to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
